						<summary>

						<p>At the entrance into the <hi rend="italic">gōpurā</hi> of the Muktīśvara Temple at Kāvēripākkam,</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Pallava Nandivaraman, Year 13 = 852 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is a fragmentary inscription. It registers a gift of five <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold, by the daughter-in-law <hi rend="italic">(marumagaḷ)</hi> of the chief Ayyakki Pangaḷa Aḍigaḷ.</p>						

						<p>[Published <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, XII No. 50.]</p>						

